===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|reyn|lang=enm}}, {{term|rein|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|reġn}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*regnaz}} (compare West Frisian {{term|rein|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|regen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Regen|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|regn|lang=da}}), from pre-Germanic {{term/t|ine-pro|*Hréǵ-no}}-, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*Hreǵ}} 'to flow' (compare Latin {{term/t|la|rigō||wet, soak}}, Lithuanian {{term|rõki|lang=lt}} 'drizzling rain', Albanian {{term|rrjedh|lang=sq}} 'to flow, drip').

